[network_virtual_node]
Processes input:
    - location: string (geographic identifier or geo-tag, e.g., 'London-DC01')
    - node_id: string (unique identifier or UUID)
Generates output:
    - encrypted_node_address: string
Implements protocol (communication standard):
    - Encrypts data using AES-256-GCM (advanced encryption standard with Galois/Counter Mode)
    - Authenticates via X.509 PKI (public key infrastructure for node-level certificates)
    - Manages sessions with mutual TLS 1.3 handshake (transport layer security protocol)
Sets dest-path: /infra/secure_nodes/${location}/${node_id}/
Enforces logging:
    - Ensures compliance with SOX (Sarbanes-Oxley Act), ISO/IEC 27001 (information security management standard)
    - Stores logs at: /audit/secure_nodes/${location}/
Activates monitoring: enabled (real-time session tracking, anomaly detection via AI, alerting systems)
Applies backup_policy: geo-replicated (multi-site redundancy), daily snapshots
Enforces security_policy: firewall + IPS (intrusion prevention system), authentication rotation, PKI enrollment, zero-trust access model
